- x and y are initialized to 1.

Now, let's analyze the loop body and make a note of the loop condition:
- The loop condition is unknown1(), which is a function whose definition is not given. We cannot make any assumptions about this function, so we cannot use it in our loop invariants.

Finally, let's output the loop invariants that are true (i) before the loop execution, (ii) in every iteration of the loop and (iii) after the loop termination, such that the loop invariants imply the post condition.

```
