    loop invariant x == y;
    loop invariant x >= 1;
    loop invariant y >= 1;
*/
```

These invariants are true before the loop execution (x and y are both initialized to 1), during every iteration of the loop (x and y are updated with the same value each iteration), and after the loop termination (the post-condition asserts y >= 1, which is implied by the loop invariants).

